5:
I shouldn't leave ALL the hard work to
everyone else... Sorry, I'm going to go
help out.
8:
You and Rooma are both members
of the Crimson Blades, so no
jumping off the ship without my
permission, all right?
17:
Ugh... Really? More shaking and
turning?
26:
Hey, kid. If you're looking for
something, I don't think I'll be much
help. Taiga hit me with something
weird—
28: Wait, is something up with Rooma?
37:
H-hey, careful! You'll get shocked if
you—
51: Alk. Vagner fell out of the sky.
54:
He sure did... But that works out for
us.
68:
Vagner, can you please take us to
Marina on your back?
73:
They won't fire if we're on you, but in
return, you have to promise you
won't attack either.
96:
Hopefully we can settle this
smoothly...
102:
Sheesh, I shouldn't have been
standing around the sidelines while
all that was going on...
107: No, it's my fault! I should have...
115:
You've got Rooma. You've got me.
You've got those stupid idiots on
both sides of the battle.
118:
But what's family without a little bit
of fighting from time to time? The
way I see it, you should give
everyone a piece of your mind.
126:
You've been keeping it in this whole
time, right? It's about time to let it all
out.
129:
Exactly. Better out than in, I always
say.
135:
I can, but... Stella and Alk are riding
on the red one... Following us... They
will catch up soon...
137:
From another direction... More
things... flying in the sky... are
coming...
142:
Hmmm... I actually just got a tip
from some drinking buddies. Seems
like a third party launched their own
attack on the lab.
146:
They drove them back, but that
Capella lady disappeared in the
chaos! Kei-Kei says she's sorry!
152:
Is it time to let loose? Or... maybe we
can still play around for a bit
longer... Hmmm...
155:
...Couette, should we keep up our
game of tag for now?
167:
But I've decided... I won't run away
anymore!
178: Alk! Stella! I won't hand Rooma over!
198: Guess we're on your side then!
206: I'm also a Crimson Blade, after all.
220:
Couette, this is from Suizen. He said
it'll come in handy.
229:
What do you think? It's Alk and
Stella! Of course they'd take your
side.
234:
Then why did we leave them
behind? Back in the lab?
238: You needed time to think, didn't you?
242:
It also wasn't a good idea to hang
around that woman's home turf.
247:
Would you kindly hand over
Armadeus? It is a danger to us all.
251:
Why don't you drop the act? You're
not fooling me.
254:
I've seen the way people get when
their eyes are focused on a prize.
Back in the lab, you lit up the second
you saw Rooma come back to you!
263:
I require the last piece of memory
you hold onto. With it, I can revive
the dark dragon Armadeus.
266:
Then I can finally fulfill the promise I
made with him.
